				"img": "icons/magic/unholy/energy-smoke-pink.webp",
				"description": "<p>You briefly go into a magical trance and whisper an alien equation which you never fully remember once the spell is complete. Each creature in the area takes 3d4 psychic damage and is deafened for 1 round.</p><p>Creatures who are unable to hear the equation, immune to psychic damage, or who have an Intelligence score lower than 4 are immune to this spell.</p><p><strong><em>Cast at Higher Levels.</em></strong> Creatures are deafened for 1 additional round for each slot level above 1st.</p>",
				"descriptionOutputs": [
					"action"
				]
			}
		},
		"description": "<p>Your brain operates on a higher level, and even powerful beings may be surprised by the complexity of what is there. You gain the following benefits:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>You gain an expertise die on all Intelligence ability checks that reference one of your skill proficiencies.</li>\n<li>When you would gain a @UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-class-features.Item.kpv6b5gtpam7cylb]{Clever Scheme} or @UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-class-features.Item.msqiaadyn4lilf8b]{Scholarly Discovery}, you can choose freely from either list. Combine your scholar and savant levels for the purpose of qualifying for any level-based prerequisites.</li>\n<li>You learn an additional @UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-class-features.Item.545vebtg2n9iqk8n]{Savant Trick} which does not count against your tricks known.</li>\n<li>You gain the following feature:</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>I Don&rsquo;t Think So</h2>\n<p>Your mind is on such an elevated level that contacting it is done at the peril of lesser beings. Creatures attempting to read your mind are affected as if you had cast @UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-spells.Item.vyneq4c6bdvado50]{Searing Equation} on them with a first-level spell slot. The save DC for this effect is your savant trick save DC. A creature that fails its save is also forcibly ejected from your mind and cannot attempt to read your thoughts for 24 hours. One that successfully saves can proceed as normal. You can intentionally suppress this effect to allow friendly creatures access to your mind (no action required) if you wish.</p>",
